      Vlaho Bukovac
      Croatian painter

      Description

      Vlaho Bukovac was a Croatian painter. His life and work were eclectic, for the artist pursued his career in a variety of locales and his style changed greatly over the course of that career. Wikipedia
      Born: July 5, 1855, Cavtat
      Died: April 23, 1922, Prague, Czechia
      On view: The Museum of Modern Art, Pavle Beljanski Memorial Collection, National Art Gallery, Walker Art Gallery
      Period: Symbolism
      Spouse: Jelica Pitarević (m. 1892–1922)
      Education: National School of Fine Arts
      Children: Ivanka Bukovac, Agostino Bukovac, Jelica Bukovac
